y" href="https://docs.ozfortress.com/rules/global"img src="https://docs.ozfortress.com/img/docs.svg" class="button-icon" /nbsp;nbsp;nbsp;Global Ruleset/anbsp;nbsp;a class="button-fancy" href="https://docs.ozfortress.com/rules/sixes"img src="https://docs.ozfortress.com/img/docs.svg" class="button-icon" /nbsp;nbsp;nbsp;Sixes Ruleset/a/divbr /div class="fancy-container"h5 class="fancy-heading"How-to Guides/h5a class="button-fancy" href="https://docs.ozfortress.com/guides/newbie_guide"img src="https://docs.ozfortress.com/img/guides.svg" class="button-icon" /nbsp;nbsp;nbsp;Newbie Guide/anbsp;nbsp;a class="button-fancy" href="https://docs.ozfortress.com/guides/book_a_server"img src="https://docs.ozfortress.com/img/guides.svg" class="button-icon" /nbsp;nbsp;nbsp;Booking an au.serveme.tf server/anbsp;nbsp;a class="button-fancy" href="https://discord.com/channels/949522376297701396/1073914845650493530"img src="https://docs.ozfortress.com/img/guides.svg" class="button-icon" /nbsp;nbsp;nbsp;Booking a Rhizome server/a/div


---

### Autumn '24 Sixes Is Here!
2024 kicks off with a bang! New year, new season, new faces, new changes.

### Signups
You can sign up for Sixes Autumn '24 (S39) from **Wednesday the 24th of January 2024**, up until **Wednesday the 7th of February 2024**. We aim to have **initial** seedings and restrictions out by **Friday the 9th of February at the latest**. The season starts **Sunday the 11th of February 2024**.

**Please see the signup agreement [here](https://ozfortress.com/forums/threads/1446) further information on helping us out with seedings!**

#### Staff Updates
Late last year we welcomed **Celph** and **Hawk** to the Sixes team, and we welcome two further additions to the Sixes Admin team, **emgee** and **HUNGRY.4.EGGS**. We do, however, say goodbye to *a team of ants in his prime* who is stepping down from his admin duties.

---

#### General Changes
- Divisions are now grouped as [Upper and Lower Divisions](https://docs.ozfortress.com/rules/global/#221-upper-and-lower-divisions).
- All competition-related communication, including match organisation, will occur in the [Team Captain Discord](https://docs.ozfortress.com/rules/global/#72-team-captain-discord). Team Captains will receive more information about this once signups conclude.
- Friday and Saturday are now considered [Secondary Match Days](https://docs.ozfortress.com/rules/global/#242-secondary-match-days).
- [Transfers](https://docs.ozfortress.com/rules/global/#5-player-transfers) are now weekly.

---

div class="news-container"div class="panel-group" id="accordion"div class="panel panel-default"div class="panel-heading"h3 class="panel-title" id="news-title"a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse_news1" class="news-link"Upper Division Changesnbsp;nbsp;i class="fa-solid fa-caret-down"/i/a/h3/divdiv id="collapse_news1" class="panel-collapse collapse"div class="panel-body"ppulliThe Upper Divisions see the departure of Reckoner and Sultry and in their place return bGranary/b and bMetalworks/b./li
liUpper Division matches during the Regular Season now follow a pick/ban system.ulliEach match has four maps available; each team eliminates one map each, with the remaining two maps being played./li/ul/li
liThe Upper Division playoffs system has been overhauled, including the pick/ban order and the system itself. Read more a href="https://docs.ozfortress.com/rules/sixes/#2-sixes-playoffs"here/a./li
lia href="https://docs.ozfortress.com/rules/global/#743-upper-division-stv-demos"STV demos/a must now be provided on match threads./ul/p/p/div/div/div/div/div

---

div class="news-container"div class="panel-group" id="accordion"div class="panel panel-default"div class="panel-heading"h3 class="panel-title" id="news-title"a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse_news2" class="news-link"Lower Division Changesnbsp;nbsp;i class="fa-solid fa-caret-down"/i/a/h3/divdiv id="collapse_news2" class="panel-collapse collapse"div class="panel-body"ppulliThe Lower Divisions* see the departure of Clearcut and Sultry and in their place return bGranary/b and bMetalworks/b.ulliAlthough Open is a Lower Division, it will feature a concentrated map pool of just seven maps. This should support newer players in learning established maps in more depth.
/li/ul/li
liFor Lower Division matches, the Progressive Ruleset Timer has been modified to only activate in the event that two teams are tied. Subsequently, the Map Timer has been changed to 30 minutes once again.
/li/ul/p/p/div/div/div/div/div


---

### Reminders

 - During Sixes Autumn '24 (S39) we plan on conducting random demo checks to ensure players are recording POV demos. Please ensure that you are recording match demos in order to avoid punishment.
 - Our rulesets have been rewritten to improve general clarity and relevance to modern ozfortress competitions as discussed [here](https://ozfortress.com/forums/threads/1462). Players should ensure they are familiar with the rule changes and should contact a League Administrator for support if necessary.
 - If you are unsure of whether or not something is considered a game exploit, contact a League Administrator for clarification. Ignorance is not an excuse.

---

